Another mechanism allowing to evade the constraint of magnetic helicity dissipation is to evacuate it through the volume boundaries. A star like the sun is not embedded in a true vaccum, and magnetic helicity can be evacuated through the corona. In particular, coronal mass ejections have been suggested to contribute significantly to the global magnetic helicity budget (Bieber and Rust 1995; Low 2001; Green et al. 2003; Lynch et al. 2005). Avoiding α\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
