Global numerical simulations of stratified rotating convection do provide additional insight on the matter. Solar-like differential rotation, in the sense of the rotation rate decreasing monotonically from the equator towards the poles, materializes when the Rossby number Ro=ut/2ΩL\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
